Differential charge density plots (isosurface value of 0.0015 eV Å−3; cyan, charge accumulation; yellow, charge depletion) of BABr and BAMeS show that the bonding between BA and MeS induces more charge redistribution than that between BA and Br.

The reaction Gibbs free energy ΔG for the reaction, CsMeS + BABr = BAMeS + CsBr, was approximated by the change of ground-state energy at 0 K: ΔG≈EBAMeS+ECsBr−EBABr−ECsMeS\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
